Perfect! Now I can see the exact bug. In the `OBJECT_AND_NON_CONCRETE` case (line ~176), the code is:

```java
return (t.getRawClass() == Object.class)
        || (!t.isConcrete()
                // [databind#88] Should not apply to JSON tree models:
        || TreeNode.class.isAssignableFrom(t.getRawClass()));
```

The comment says "Should not apply to JSON tree models" but the code uses `||` (OR) with `TreeNode.class.isAssignableFrom(t.getRawClass())`, meaning it WILL apply to JSON tree models, which is wrong.

It should be `&& !(TreeNode.class.isAssignableFrom(t.getRawClass()))` to exclude TreeNode types, just like in the `NON_FINAL` case.

